article.description: Bryson Williams scored 19 points on 7-for-11 shooting as UTEP topped New Mexico State 65-50 on Tuesday night.
article.headline: Williams scores 19 to lift UTEP over New Mexico St. 65-50
article.linkText: Williams scores 19 to lift UTEP over New Mexico St. 65-50
article.story: EL PASO, Texas -- Bryson Williams scored 19 points on 7-for-11 shooting as UTEP topped New Mexico State 65-50 on Tuesday night. Jordan Lathon had 13 points for UTEP (2-0), which made 23 of 49 shots (47-%). Trevelin Queen had 21 points for the Aggies (1-1), who were held to 37-% shooting and converted just two of 11 free throws. Terrell Brown added 10 points. The Miners scored 22 points off 16 Aggies turnovers and owned a 34-28 edge in points in the paint despite being outrebounded, 39-33. UTEP plays Eastern New Mexico at home on Friday. New Mexico State takes on Southern at home on Thursday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
